This paper presents a framework for trajectory optimization for wheeled quadrupedal robots capable of executing hybrid walking-driving locomotion strategies. The paper focuses on the development of a real-time model predictive control system for the robot, which suggests that it falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also mentions the use of a hierarchical whole-body controller, which suggests that it may also fall under the categories of systems and control (cs.SY) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of mapping and exploration in dynamic underground environments, which suggests that it may fall under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV).
